This paper proposes a novel attention mechanism for natural language processing tasks, which is a popular research area in computer science. The paper focuses on improving the performance of sentence encoding methods, which is a subfield of natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper proposes a neural network architecture that does not use RNN or CNN structures, which suggests that it may also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
